
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Elderly Home Management System

class Department {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -rooms: Set<Room>
}

class Room {
  -id: int
  -number: int
  -beds: Set<Bed>
}

class Bed {
  -id: int
  -category: Category
  -isOccupied: boolean
}

class Category {
  -id: int
  -type: String (RH, RNH, SF)
  -pricePerDay: float
}

class Inhabitant {
  -id: int
  -name: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -registrationDate: Date
  -waitingListPosition: int
  -stays: Set<Stay>
}

class Stay {
  -id: int
  -startDate: Date
  -endDate: Date
  -category: Category
  -bed: Bed
  -status: String (active, suspended, ended)
  -invoices: Set<Invoice>
}

class WaitingList {
  -inhabitants: List<Inhabitant>
}

class Invoice {
  -id: int
  -date: Date
  -amount: float
  -outstandingAmount: float
  -status: String (pending, paid)
  -stay: Stay
}

class PaymentEvent {
  -id: int
  -date: Date
  -amount: float
  -invoice: Invoice
}

class Assessment {
  -id: int
  -date: Date
  -category: Category
  -inhabitant: Inhabitant
}

class CreditNote {
  -id: int
  -amount: float
  -date: Date
  -paymentEvent: PaymentEvent
}

' Relationships

Department "1" --> "0..*" Room
Room "1" --> "0..*" Bed
Bed "1" --> "1" Category
Inhabitant "1" --> "0..*" Stay
Inhabitant "1" --> "0..1" Assessment
Stay "1" --> "1" Category
Stay "1" --> "0..*" Invoice
Invoice "1" --> "1" Stay
PaymentEvent "1" --> "1" Invoice
CreditNote "1" --> "1" PaymentEvent
Assessment "1" --> "1" Inhabitant
WaitingList "1" --> "0..*" Inhabitant
@enduml

---

### ✅ Summary of Classes:

- **Department**: Manages rooms.
- **Room**: Contains beds.
- **Bed**: Belongs to a category and can be occupied or not.
- **Category**: Defines types of stays (RH, RNH, SF) with price per day.
- **Inhabitant**: Has multiple stays and may be on a waiting list.
- **Stay**: Represents a period in a specific category with associated invoices.
- **Invoice**: Generated monthly, can be modified until paid.
- **PaymentEvent**: Records payments made by inhabitants.
- **CreditNote**: Created when an overpayment occurs.
- **Assessment**: Determines the appropriate stay type for an inhabitant.
- **WaitingList**: Maintains inhabitants waiting for a bed of a specific category.

